<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="1043" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1043">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/1432</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Postmaster General</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BAS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Burleson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-30">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 31</hi>.] </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your letter of the 26th instant, enclosing a copy of a
                                letter from Frank A. Page, Industrial Trust Building, Providence,
                                Rhode Island, relative to the importation by parcel post from
                                Germany of articles of German origin.<note n="2" xml:id="d1043fn2">Not printed.</note>
                            </p>
                            <pb facs="0991" n="733" xml:id="pg_733"/>
                            <p>In reply, I have to inform you that the parcel-post service is in
                                operation between the United States and Germany, the parcel-post
                                mails for and from Germany being dispatched via Rotterdam.</p>
                            <p>The Department has no reason to believe that parcel-post mails from
                                Germany for this country or from this country for Germany have been
                                interfered with by any intervening country.</p>
                            <p>By direction of the Postmaster General.</p>
                            <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_FAA1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. A. Fisher</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Acting Second Assistant Postmaster General</hi>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>